  Sources. This dataset is built on two official sources, in this order: the
  legal act first, and the ministry's implementation materials combined on top.
  Every outcome is tagged with which source it came from.

  (1) Riigi Teataja — the foundation. The binding national curriculum (riiklik
  õppekava, a Vabariigi Valitsuse määrus) and its appendices (lisad) define the
  subject structure and the learning outcomes. As a public legal act, its text
  is excluded from copyright protection under §5 of the Estonian Copyright Act
  (Autoriõiguse seadus). The dataset is verified complete against this act:
  every õpitulemus in the act is present in the data.

  (2) OKMV (Õppekava materjalide veeb,
  https://projektid.edu.ee/spaces/OKMV/overview), maintained by the Estonian
  Ministry of Education and Research (Haridus- ja Teadusministeerium) — the
  implementation layer combined onto the legal-act base: the grade-by-grade
  distribution of the learning outcomes, recommended teaching content
  (soovituslik õppesisu), and methodological guidance (soovituslikud juhised),
  for the curricula in effect since March 2023. These are the ministry's
  official implementation materials, reused here with attribution.

  This repository's contribution is combining the two into one machine-readable
  dataset: stable identifiers, the structuring, the coverage verification
  against the act, and the derived exports.

  When attributing this dataset, please credit Praktikal and the sources
  (Haridus- ja Teadusministeerium; Riigi Teataja / projektid.edu.ee).

  If you are a rights holder with a concern about any material here, please open
  an issue and we will address it promptly.

